    {
      "id": "el_10",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1005,
      "y": 100,
      "width": 412,
      "height": 22,
      "text": "HCF & LCM of Fractions",
      "fontSize": 17,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 17,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 1000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 10,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "HCF & LCM of Fractions",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_11",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1005,
      "y": 125,
      "width": 414,
      "height": 266,
      "text": "HCF of fractions:\n  = HCF of numerators / LCM of denominators\n\nLCM of fractions:\n  = LCM of numerators / HCF of denominators\n\nExample: HCF(2/3, 4/9)\n  = HCF(2,4) / LCM(3,9) = 2/9\n\nExample: LCM(2/3, 4/9)\n  = LCM(2,4) / HCF(3,9) = 4/3\n\nWHY: HCF of fracs must divide all → smallest num(HCF)\n  over largest den(LCM). LCM reverses the logic.\n\nEx: HCF(1/2, 1/3) = HCF(1,1)/LCM(2,3) = 1/6\n  Verify: (1/2)÷(1/6)=3✓ (1/3)÷(1/6)=2✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 1100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 11,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "HCF of fractions:\n  = HCF of numerators / LCM of denominators\n\nLCM of fractions:\n  = LCM of numerators / HCF of denominators\n\nExample: HCF(2/3, 4/9)\n  = HCF(2,4) / LCM(3,9) = 2/9\n\nExample: LCM(2/3, 4/9)\n  = LCM(2,4) / HCF(3,9) = 4/3\n\nWHY: HCF of fracs must divide all → smallest num(HCF)\n  over largest den(LCM). LCM reverses the logic.\n\nEx: HCF(1/2, 1/3) = HCF(1,1)/LCM(2,3) = 1/6\n  Verify: (1/2)÷(1/6)=3✓ (1/3)÷(1/6)=2✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
