      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: N÷6, N÷9, N÷12 all give rem 5\n  So N-5 is divisible by 6, 9, and 12\nStep 2: N-5 = LCM(6,9,12) = 36\n  N = 36+5 = 41\n\nTRICK (same remainder rule):\nN = LCM(divisors) + R\n= LCM(6,9,12) + 5 = 36+5 = 41\n\n  ┌─────────────────────────┐\n  │  N-5 divisible by all   │\n  │  N-5 = LCM = 36        │\n  │  N = 41                 │\n  └─────────────────────────┘\n\nVerify: 41/6=6r5✓ 41/9=4r5✓ 41/12=3r5✓\n\nAnswer: Smallest number = 41 ✓",
